<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-344] Out-dated Lustre build instructions</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-344</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;m compiling Lustre 2.8 for CentOS 7.2 lastest kernel.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And found that the instructions from &quot;Walk-thru- Build Lustre MASTER on RHEL 6.4/CentOS 6.4 from Whamcloud git&quot; are not applicable to newer kernels. In particular, the following steps fail:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;make include/asm&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;make include/linux/version.h&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;make SUBDIRS=scripts&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;make include/linux/utsrelease.h&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;with &quot;No rule to make target&quot; error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What is the latest information for building Lustre from source?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>CentOS Linux release 7.2.1511; kernel-3.10.0-327.22.2.el7</environment>
